: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, Ramadan is a month in which Allah Almighty has obligated its fasting. I have instituted for Muslims the practice of prayer at night. Thus, whoever fasts it with faith and expecting reward will\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5250,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/17\/fasting-ramadan-six-shawwal\/","url_meta":{"origin":37804,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: Recommendation to fast six days of Shawwal","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 17, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Ayyub reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever fasts the month of Ramadan and then follows it with six days of fasting in the month of Shawwal, it will be as if he has fasted for the entire year.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1164\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3705,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/18\/siyam-salat-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":37804,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: Reward of fasting and praying in Ramadan","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 18, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever fasts the month of Ramadan due to faith and seeking reward, his previous sins will be forgi